1 by trauma;
2 2. Identify ways to recognize and respond to mental health issues in all
3 students; and
4 3. Identify ways to build resiliency and wellness in all students.
5 (d) Each school counselor or school-based mental health services provider
6 providing services pursuant to this section, and the trauma-informed team
7 members described in paragraph (b) of this subsection, shall provide training,
8 guidance, and assistance to other administrators, teachers, and staff on:
9 1. Recognizing symptoms of trauma in students;
10 2. Utilizing interventions and strategies to support the learning needs of
